The Nigeria Police Force, Borno State command, has confirmed that no fewer than 55 scrap metal collectors lost their lives in a series of attacks coordinated by the Boko Haram insurgents in the last three weeks in the state.The Commissioner of Police in the state, Abdu Umar, made this known while speaking on the sideline of a security stakeholders’ meeting on Saturday in Maiduguri. IGP Usman Baba Alkali



The stakeholders included the police, the Nigerian Army, the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), and Department of State Security (DSS) among others.SaharaReporters had on June 9 exclusively reported that the militants from the Islamic State-backed faction of Boko Haram, the Islamic State West Africa Province (ISWAP), formerly known as Jamā'at Ahl as-Sunnah lid-Da'wah wa'l-Jihād, killed at least 23 metal scavengers along Boboshe village in Dikwa LGA of Borno State.Two people escaped the attack while seven others remained missing, a military source had told SaharaReporters. See Also






